<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>7.3 Liter Diesel Engine Service (1991) - CONNECTING RODS, PISTONS AND RINGS - CONNECTING RODS, PISTONS AND
        RINGS REMOVAL &#38; REASSEMBLY - Inspection
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="proctype" graphiccount="0">
        <title>Inspection</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Visually inspect the connecting rod, bolts and nuts for nicks or damage.</para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>When lubricated with clean engine oil, the nuts must screw onto the bolts by hand. If the nut
                        will not screw in by hand, discard and use new nuts and bolts.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Visually inspect the pistons for scuffed or scored skirts and cracked or worn lands. Replace
                the piston as required.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Refer to Piston and Ring Inspection in this section.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
